# Line-ending policy.
# Git on Windows converts LF -> CRLF on checkout, which rewrites the bytes
# of every source file and changes the `data` hash in the build stamp.
# A fresh clone would then build to a different hash than production for no
# reason but line endings, and the fingerprint would stop meaning anything.
# So: no conversion anywhere in this repo.
*               -text
*.ttf           binary
*.wasm          binary
*.onnx          binary
*.png           binary
*.ico           binary
*.zip           binary
